pect of the game.  Jubal is probably receiving high praise from those who want this, but those that don't seem to be getting a little overshadowed.  I agree, its probably a nice idea if it works, and as you will still have limited powers to make any real changes, its still not going to stop the d00d banter and KS'ing of old.<br>
<br>
My point basically is, the Blue Dragons as a guild met and discussed the events that took place in Solusek and decided that we did not want to add more rules to a game already clogged with rules and nerfing.  We wanted to continue as we were and just enjoy the guild participation that we have, and the nice friendly family type relationship that our members have.  We do not wish to be governed by RP guilds with egotistical ideas.<br>
<br>
I want the Law Collective to realise that many guilds will choose not to follow suit, and as such cannot be blacklisted or blackmarked for their actions if they do not agree to enter in the roleplay scenario that is currently being formed.  We just want to be able to log on after a tiring day of RL and relax into our virtual environment without any in your face roleplaying fanatics throwing around rules of how we should play.<br>
<br>
I imagine the rp guilds will press to have guilds like ours moved to the new server in the split as they will feel that we dont fit, but to be honest, we are on Fennin, we like Fennin and if anyone wants to change things, then go elsewhere to do it.  Make the new split server the roleplaying haven that you dreamed of and let Fennin remain as it is... A nice peaceful, no pressure server full of people that we know.<br>
<br>
Kyte <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utamboran.showPublicProfile>Tamboran</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.mindspring.com/~rmcelreath/note.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/00 11:39:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Law Collective and those not interested</span><hr size=1> We have already spoken on the Collective board, and I was just checking through here and saw that your concerns are over here as well.  And I'm pretty sure that Jythri and Jubal do not come over here.<br>
<br>
I want to emphasize that Common Law will not affect you at all if you do not wish to participate.  It is merely a drawing board for sagas and stories for us, it gives us more of a background than what was given to us by Verant.  If you do not wish to participate in CL, you will not be blacklisted, and you will not be asked to move to the new server.<br>
<br>
We are not moving to the new server, because there is always the chance that we will lose someone, which is probably the same reason the Blue Dragons will not be moving.  We CAN live peacefully together.<br>
<br>
And as to the OOC Blacklisting that everybody is so upset about, here is what we plan on doing for that at the current moment.  The only reason anybody would even be blacklisted would be if they REPEATEDLY KS different members of the Collective, or otherwise do things ON PURPOSE to make the game less fun for those in the Collective, and even then it needs to have several witnesses and happen multiple times.<br>
<br>
This way, JoeSchmo can't join the collective and say &quot;Tamboran KS'd me when I was hunting froglok tads in Innothule repeatedly&quot; and have me blacklisted.<br>
<br>
And, as I mentioned before, we probably have 400 or so people doing CL, and there are 2500-3000 people on the server...Odds are, you'll still get SoW'd or healed!  I wouldn't worry about it.<br>
<br>
So, to re-emphasize, Common Law will help those that want to be a part of it, and will not do anything to those that don't want to be a part of it.<br>
<br>
